1、什么是面向对象？


2、面向对象的重要设计原则
        SOLID is the mnemonic acronym introduced by Michael Feathers for the first five principles named by Robert Martin, which meant five basic principles of object-oriented programming and design.
        S：职责单一原则（SRP）（Single Responsibility Principle）
        O：开闭原则（OCP）（Open/Close Principle）
                软件实体（类、模块、功能等）应该对扩展开发，对修改关闭
                software entities (classes, modules, functions, etc.) should be open for extension, but closed for modification
        L：里氏替换原则（LSP）（Liskov Substritution Principle）
        I：接口隔离原则（ISP）（Interface Segregation Principle）
                客户不应该被强制依赖于他们用不到的接口
                Clients should not be forced to depend upon interfaces that they do not use.
        D：依赖反转原则（DIP）（Dependency Inversion Principle）
                高级模块不应该依赖于低级模块，两者都应该依赖于抽象；               
                High-level modules should not depend on low-level modules. Both should depend on abstractions.
                抽象类不应依赖于实例，实例应该依赖于抽象
               Abstractions should not depend upon details. Details should depend on abstractions.
